@node demo "DEMO Limitations"

As you surely noticed, this is only a demo.
To get the full version you have to @{"register" link reg}.

The following things are different in the demo:
   - there is an annoying requester that will appear at startup
      and quit, the requester blocks for 10 seconds
   - you can request only one url at a time
   - registred users get a personal keyfile
   - importing from clipboard is not available
   - no rexx port
   - no example rexx scripts
   - no shell interface
   - no instructions how to bind AmiURLRequester into your browser
   - no support mailing list
   - no locale support

To get rid of all this limitations, @{"register" link reg} and get the full version.

@endnode

@node intro "Introduction"

We surfers all know this, we have found a file that we wanna have,
but this file is very big and the server is awfully slow. Well,
the guys from Downloadslave (http://www.downloadslave.com) know
this situation, too. So they set up a service, that downloads
the file for you and sends it to your email address. You will
never have slow downloads again!

A friend told me about this service and I decided to give it a chance,
but I had to discover that the equest has to be send by mail, which
is very uncomfortable. The PC lamers have a program called URLRequester,
that writes the request mail and sends it to Downloadslave, but I haven't
found a AMIGA program that does this, so I decided to write my own...
The result is AmiURLRequester!

@endnode

@node feat "Features"

The features of AmiURLRequester are:
   - a easy to use MUI GUI
   - you can import urls from the clipboard (*)
   - a powerful rexx port (*)
   - example rexx scripts (*)
   - many other things that you have to discover yourself... :^)

(*) = registered version only

@endnode

@node req "Requierements"

You'll need:
   - MUI 3.5 or higher
   - a tcp/ip stack
   - a big email account ;-)

@endnode

@node install "Installation"

Copy the AmiURLRequester directory everywhere you want.
Copy your personal keyfile to S:.

@endnode

@node config "Configuration"

To open the config window, click on the menupoint "Settings..." in the
"Settings" menu.

@{u}Your eMail address:@{uu}
   Type in your email address here. All requested files will be sent to
   this address.

@{u}Downloadslave pass:@{uu}
   Type in your downloadslave pass, that you received from Downloadslave.
   (see "Request pass" button)

@{u}Your smtp server:@{uu}
   The name of your smtp server.

@{u}Request pass:@{uu}
   Click on this button to request a pass from Downloadslave.
   You need a pass to make requests, if you forgot your pass,
   click on this button and you'll get it again.
   After the pass request is sent you'll get a message from
   Downloadslave that contains your pass, type it in the field
   "Downloadslave pass".
   @{b}NOTE:@{ub}
      The fields smtp server and email address must contain correct
      values!

@{u}Save:@{uu}
   Save your settings.

@{u}Use:@{uu}
   Use your settings without saving.

@endnode

@node usage "Usage"

@{u}Menu:@{uu}

   @{u}Project:@{uu}

      @{u}Request:@{uu}
         send a request to Downloadslave.

      @{u}About:@{uu}
         open the about window.

      @{u}Quit:@{uu}
         quit the program.

   @{u}Settings:@{uu}

      @{u}Settings:@{uu}
         open the @{"config" link config} window.

      @{u}MUI settings:@{uu}
         open the MUI settings editor.


@{u}Main window:@{uu}

   @{u}urls listview:@{uu}
      Every url you want to request is displayed here.

   @{u}string gadget:@{uu}
      Type in every url that you want to request.
      You can request every http:// or ftp:// url.

   @{u}Import:@{uu} (*)
      Import a url from clipboard.
      NOTE: urls are always imported from clipboard unit 0!
            Only urls that begin with "http://" or "ftp://"
            are imported, other strings are ignored.

   @{u}Remove:@{uu}
      Remove a url from the listview.
      Select a url in the listview and click on Remove.

   @{u}Status bar:@{uu}
      Progress information or errors are displayed in the status bar.

   @{u}Request:@{uu}
      Send a request to Downloadslave.

   @{u}Cancel:@{uu}
      Quit the program.

   @{u}Abort transfer:@{uu}
      While a request is send, click on this button to abort it.
      The program may block for a while, if a server lag occures.
      The timeout is set to one minute, this means that after 60
      seconds of quietness on the socket, the transfer is
      automatically aborted.

(*) = only available in registered version

@endnode

@node reg "Register"

The shareware fee is $15 or 15DM (or the correspondenting value in your
currency). Methods of payment are cash, cheque, travelers cheque or bank
transfer (only inside Germany!).

To register, select in the menu "Projects" the menu point "Register...".
In the register window, please fill out all fields and select your prefered
pay method. Instructions where to send the money are displayed in the little
info text field right down the payment field.

As soon as I or the Northern American registration site receive your registration,
you'll receive first your personal keyfile and an hour later the registered version.

@{b}Please register to support me and the AMIGA!@{ub}

@endnode

@node hist "History"

V1.0ß (28-11-98)
   - first release

V1.0 (10-01-99)
   - "Request password" works now
   - maximum chars in the url input gadget is now 256 chars
   - urls, that were not requested are saved and at the next
     start of AmiURLRequester shown in the urls list.
   - replaced progressbar by a status line
   - fixed some minor bugs

V1.01 (15-01-99)
   - fixed some heavy bugs

V2.0 (10-7-99)
   - completly rewritten in C, bye bye good old ARexx
   - MUI GUI
   - decided to release it as shareware
   - import urls from clipboard
   - rexx interface
   - example rexx scripts
   - abort transfer button
   - improved menu and GUI
   - some bugs were fixed
   - catalogs are now used
   - many many other things...

@endnode

@node fut "Future"

Well, the future of AmiURLRequester is written in the stars,
nothing yet is planned. If you have some ideas or have complains
about bugs, send me or the @{"mailing list" link list} a message.

@endnode

